  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help communities to conserve Peru&apos;s Dry Forests</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Peru&apos;s coastal dry forests are currently threatened, impacting biodiversity and the vulnerability of the low-income communities that depend on them. This project will educate 200 community members in La Libertad, Peru, to conserve, protect and sustainably manage over 1350 hectares of dry forest habitat. Specifically, this project will deliver 24 capacity building workshops, reforest 3 hectares of land, install 10 fuel efficient cookstoves, and create opportunities for sustainable livelihoods.</narrative>
  </description>
